{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionIn recent years, the domain of information retrieval has witnessed significant advancements with the advent of Large Language Models (LLMs), which have transformed the landscape of natural language understanding and generation, offering unprecedented capabilities in processing complex linguistic data [1].",
    "However, the challenge of accurately aligning retrieved information with specific user queries remains a critical issue in the field.",
    "Traditional information retrieval systems, primarily based on keyword matching and statistical approaches, have shown limitations in understanding the context and nuances of user queries [2,3,4,5].",
    "The emergence of LLMs promised to overcome these limitations by leveraging deep learning techniques for a more nuanced understanding of language, but despite their advanced capabilities, they often struggle to retrieve information that precisely matches the complexity and specificity of user inquiries [6,1].The LLaMA model, as a prominent example of LLMs, embodies the strides made in natural language processing.",
    "Nevertheless, it too faces challenges in achieving optimal accuracy in information retrieval."
  ]
}